        <h2>The Environmental Pillar</h2>
        <p>Environmental sustainability is usualy the most focused/the most thought of when
            someone
            mentions
            the word sustainability,
            and with good reason for an individual could not sustain itself without first have a
            sustainable
            environment/place.</p>
        <p>An healthy ecosystem is imperative in order to provide vital goods and services to
            humans and
            other
            organisms. </p>
        <p>So in order for us to strive, we must reduce the negative impact our actions can
            cause.</p>
        <p>For that there are several approaches we can take such as environmental resource
            management,
            management
            of human consumption of resources, recycling, etc.</p>
