        <p><strong>Recycling</strong> is the process of converting waste materials into new
            materials or
            objects,
            allowing us to reutilize what was once unusable so that may not need to take more
            from the
            environment
            while redirecting the waste outputs out of the economic system.</p>
        <p>It serves as an alternative to "conventional" waste disposal and contributes a lot to
            lowering
            the
            greenhouse
            gas emissions.</p>
        <p>Recycle has become a key component in modern day society and is the third action of
            the "Reduce,
            Reuse, and
            Recycle" waste hierarchy.</p>
        <p>This simple three word quote is used as a way to imprint a message onto society, that
            we should
            be
            moderate
            with what we use, reuse it if possible and not just discard it away after just a few
            times, and
            finally
            to turn it into something new so once again may continue its repeating cycle.</p>
        <p>Nowadays, there are several materials that can and should be recycled such as many
            kinds of
            glass,
            paper,
            cardboard, metal, plastic, tires, textiles, batteries, and even electronics.</p>
        <p>But recycling isnt the only way to make use of non-usable materials/products, there
            are other
            ways
            to help the
            environment.</p>
        <br />
        <p><strong>Composting </strong> is another way of using no longer needed materials, it
            is often
            used on
            various organic materials that would be otherwise regarded as waste and instead it
            is used as
            soil conditioner. Compost is rich in nutrients and is used on various places such as
            gardens,
            agriculture,
            landscaping, etc.</p>
